sec.p:
We measured the following environmental variables potentially affecting bird species richness (number of species) and abundance (number of individuals recorded in study squares): 





type of environment: urban or rural;
    



cover (%) within the square of: trees, amenity grass, arable, fallow, meadows, buildings and roads, water;
    



number of bird feeders;
    



human population size in the urban area;
    



geographical latitude and longitude.
